This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation and post-editing. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to analyze and represent human post-editors, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of human behavior and interaction with technology, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
